# Test Auth API Endpoints

## Base URL
http://localhost:5000

## 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

## 2. Register User
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "test123",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

## 3. Login User
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "test123"
}

## 4. Get Current User (Protected)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

## 5. Update Profile (Protected)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fullName": "Updated Name",
  "avatar": "/assets/images/avatars/avatar2.png"
}

## 6. Update Settings (Protected)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/auth/settings
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "backgroundMusic": true,
  "soundEffects": true,
  "timer": true,
  "questionsPerExam": 10,
  "examTimer": 45,
  "selectedAvatar": "avatar3"
}

## 7. Change Password (Protected)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/auth/password
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "test123",
  "newPassword": "newpass123"
}
